title: Mohamad Ali Vaez
text:
Mohamad Ali Vaez (born April 5, 1979), is an American <a href="professional%20wrestler">professional wrestler</a>, who is best known for his time spent in <a href="Ohio%20Valley%20Wrestling">Ohio Valley Wrestling</a> and <a href="Global%20Force%20Wrestling">Global Force Wrestling</a>.
Professional wrestling career.
Global Force Wrestling (2015).
On July 24, 2015, Vaez made his <a href="Global%20Force%20Wrestling">Global Force Wrestling</a> (GFW) debut under the ring name Ali Akbar as part of the <a href="List%20of%20Global%20Force%20Wrestling%20tournaments%23GFW%20Tag%20Team%20Championship%20Tournament%20%282015%29">GFW Tag Team Championship Tournament</a> during the "<a href="Impact%20One%20Night%20Only%20%282017%29%23GFW%20Amped%20Anthology%20%E2%80%93%20Part%201">GFW Amped</a>" tapings as part of the tag team The Akbars with Omar Akbar losing to <a href="The%20Bollywood%20Boyz">The Bollywood Boyz</a> in the quarterfinals.
On August 14, 2015, Akbar teamed with <a href="Cliff%20Compton">Cliff Compton</a> and <a href="Jason%20Kincaid">Jason Kincaid</a> in a losing effort against Brad Attitude, Peter Kaasa and <a href="Vordell%20Walker">Vordell Walker</a> during the "GFW Grand Slam Tour" in <a href="Winston-Salem%2C%20North%20Carolina">Winston-Salem, North Carolina</a>.
On August 21, 2015, The Akbars teamed with <a href="PJ%20Black">PJ Black</a> during the "<a href="Impact%20One%20Night%20Only%20%282017%29%23GFW%20Amped%20Anthology%20%E2%80%93%20Part%202">GFW Amped</a>" tapings defeating the team of <a href="Sonjay%20Dutt">Sonjay Dutt</a> and <a href="Los%20Luchas">Los Luchas</a> (Phoenix Star and Zokre)
On August 28 and 29, 2015 during the "GFW Grand Slam Tour" in <a href="Harrisburg%2C%20Pennsylvania">Harrisburg, Pennsylvania</a> and <a href="Richmond%2C%20Virginia">Richmond, Virginia</a>, Akbar teamed with <a href="Seiya%20Sanada">Seiya Sanada</a> in two on one handicap matches against <a href="Luke%20Gallows">Doc Gallows</a> in a losing effort on both nights.
